claim.claim-text:
1. A computerized gaming method operated by a gaming machine comprising:
causing a first video image to be generated on a display associated with a gaming machine using one or more processors of said gaming machine, said first video image representing a first game selected from a group of first games consisting of video poker, video blackjack, video slots, video keno and video bingo;
causing a second video image of a second game to be generated on a display associated with a gaming machine using said one or more processors of said gaming machine, said second game comprising an instant bonus game;
allowing said instant bonus game to be purchased for a buy-in amount and played without requiring play of said first game and without first obtaining a win in said first game using said one or more processors of said gaming machine, wherein said instant bonus game is the same whether earned or purchased;
setting odds of winning said instant bonus game, using said one or more processors of said gaming machine, to be the same whether said instant bonus game was earned or purchased; and
determining, using said one or more processors of said gaming machine, a value payout associated with said instant bonus game after said instant bonus game is played by a player.

9. A computerized gaming method operated by a gaming machine comprising:
performing a first attraction sequence related to a first game using one or more processors of said gaming machine;
causing a first video image to be generated on a display associated with a gaming machine using said one or more processors of said gaming machine, said first video image representing said first game selected from a group of first games consisting of video poker, video blackjack, video slots, video keno and video bingo;
performing a second attraction sequence related to a second game using said one or more processors of said gaming machine;
causing a second video image of said second game to be generated on a display associated with a gaming machine using said one or more processors of said gaming machine, said second game comprising an instant bonus game;
allowing said instant bonus game to be purchased for a buy-in amount and played without requiring play of said first game and without first obtaining a win in said first game using said one or more processors of said gaming machine, wherein said instant bonus game is the same whether earned or purchased;
setting odds of winning said instant bonus game to be the same whether said instant bonus game was earned or purchased using said one or more processors of said gaming machine; and
determining, using said one or more processors of said gaming machine, a value payout associated with said instant bonus game after said instant bonus game is played by a player.

19. A non-transitory computer readable medium comprising instructions, which when implemented by one or more processors perform the following operations:
cause a first video image to be generated, said first video image representing a first game selected from a group of first games consisting of video poker, video blackjack, video slots, video keno and video bingo;
cause a second video image of a second game to be generated, said second game comprising an instant bonus game;
allow said instant bonus game to be purchased for a buy-in amount and played without requiring play of said first game and without first obtaining a win in said first game, wherein said instant bonus game is the same whether earned or purchased;
set odds of winning said instant bonus game to be the same whether said instant bonus game was earned or purchased; and
determine a value payout associated with said instant bonus game after said instant bonus game is played by a player.

20. A non-transitory computer readable medium comprising instructions, which when implemented by one or more processors perform the following operations:
perform a first attraction sequence related to a first game;
cause a first video image to be generated, said first video image representing said first game selected from a group of first games consisting of video poker, video blackjack, video slots, video keno and video bingo;
perform a second attraction sequence related to a second game;
cause a second video image of said second game to be generated, said second game comprising an instant bonus game;
allow said instant bonus game to be purchased for a buy-in amount and played without requiring play of said first game and without first obtaining a win in said first game, wherein said instant bonus game is the same whether earned or purchased;
set odds of winning said instant bonus game to be the same whether said instant bonus game was earned or purchased; and
determine a value payout associated with said instant bonus game after said instant bonus game is played by a player.
